Fandom Secrets
{{WP80}}
{{needsmoar|tragically sad secrets}}

[[image:whatareyoudoing.jpg|right|thumb|400px|This sums up the community nicely. [http://community.livejournal.com/fandomsecrets/112439.html?thread=27177015#t27177015 This person] has admitted to making it, defeating the point of it being a "secret."]]
Just as [[NORP|normal]] bourgeois citizens confess their banal stories of [[lonely]] and [[fail|failure]] to [[PostSecret]], [[Otaku]] and [[Wapanese]] send their own, far more pathetic, tales to the [[Livejournal]] community [http://community.livejournal.com/fandomsecrets/ '''fandomsecrets'''.] 

What is '''Fandom Secrets''' made of?

*'''28%''' of the secrets are about how two lesbians roleplaying yaoibuttsex fall in love with each other.
*'''12%''' consists of lesbians getting dumped by their yaoibuttsex RP girlfriends. 
*'''The rest''' are [[vomit|heart-wrenching]] confessions about how two characters in some [[anime]] thing didn't end up together, or how a character died and it made the poster cry for weeks, or something equally [[lame]], or how someone wants to screw a character whose name they picked out of a hat for the lulz. 

==A Lonely Existence==
[[Image:PuttPuttWUT.jpg|thumb|left|... There are no words.]]
Every single post in there was written from the depths of a [[basement dweller|lightless basement]] on a keyboard sticky with crumbs, tears, and [[cum|grease]].

The comments for each posted secret are even worse, if such a thing is possible, and it has been established that each [[Moderator]] there is likely to be a [http://community.livejournal.com/fandomsecrets/104153.html cunty elitist asshole (scroll down)] and possibly even [[bisexual]]. Very [[bisexual]]. This caused much [[Internet drama]], [[Lulz]] and [[Wank]]. [http://technophile.livejournal.com One of the mods] and [http://failaga.livejournal.com the resident pedo of the secret LB organization] have even been rumored to be [[canon]] and were a very popular pairing at [http://community.livejournal.com/missedgebitch/633.html?thread=152441#t152441 this OTP meme.]  But they're not actually a [[gay]] couple, since they're both just [[fangirls]] roleplaying [[yaoi]] because none of the boys in their high school will [[fuck|date]] them. Clearly an example of [[aids|bad breeding]] and [[failure]].

Unknown to most, although the community is supposedly run by three [[16 year old girls]], [http://community.livejournal.com/fandomsecrets fandomsecrets] is in fact run by a [[gay|shady]] [[internet]] [[circle_jerk|organization]] known as [http://lolbuttsex.livejournal.com "LB."] Any [[fag|members]] that voice dissent about either the [[moderator]]s' opinions or how the community is run are either quickly silenced, [[gangbang|gangbanged]] into submission, or [[anal_sex|made offers they can't refuse]]. And by means of ridiculously vague "rules" regarding what secrets are and are not posted, this [[circle_jerk|organization]] of [[retard|drooling]] [[fangirl|fangirls]] suppresses all secrets that might possibly go against [[homosexual agenda|the gay agenda]].

[[Idiots]] are prone to calling it fandom_secrets when there really is no underscore.  Putting in the underscore will take you to an even [[fail|shittier]] copycat community that nobody joined but the mod's friends.  It got changed to tv_secret once the mod realized how stupid they were for not checking before creating the community.

